content: I would like to know if i can change my element or not
Really great book, the ending focuses on what really is important in life.
A great but short story imo. Didn't feel like I was rushed through. A simple character design. Overall, a great way to past the time on a long flight
Really enjoyed it looking forward to seeing more

I would have liked the story if you hadnt killed off the only character i liked throwing me in a random ass timeline that isnt explained at all doesnt redeem patches death at all and the makes no sense hes asked a question and poof hes in an alternate reality with no goal and somehow he already stops his impending doom

You dont get a choice on what the character thinks, feels, and says. You don't even have a choice on what happens on the story. I wanted to play as a money hungry mercenary but the character is automatically some "honorable" tryhard. Me giving this game 2 stars is VERY generous. At least in Hyuga your choices aren't really forced. This is definitely a dumb down.
It was a good interesting story but it was waaaaay to short
Great ending, if a sequel was made I want balance between a wedding set up in this stories end. Bad things happen to popular places. That's your sequel 😉

This story ruined my life. As an avid follower of these stories, to say I was excited to start Fatehaven, was an understatement. As soon as I started reading, I knew I had found something special. I admit, I have a weakness for anything that involves magic, particularly that of element magic, but Fatehaven does more than just tell a tale of a mage who seeks to avenge their beloved. The ending of the book leaves me feeling as if I will never read something quite this exciting ever again. Get it.
It was awesome! I absolutely loved it! Though, I wish it would have gotten a more graph if you on what I mean.
Great story, good at connecting the reader and emotions of the reader to the story. It's a must read interactive novel
Not really what I expected, for I was looking for a similar experience to Samurai of Hyuga from the same author; not a bad game nonetheless, just feels a bit more like Life of a Wizard.
Stat Screen is currently broken so playing is more difficult since I can't see half my stats, but good game otherwise.
It's humorous and well written, memorable characters and an interesting premise!

Mediocre writing with a very unnecessary "twist ending" that is clever, but takes all agency out of the player's hands, rendering choices largely meaningless. It might be a good story, but not a good choice-based choose your own adventure game.

I give a four because it's fun, creative, and challenging BUT I can't get achievements which makes it less challenging than the others. I'll still go through to beat it and get all reknown and find the last element but I won't be interested for much longer.
One the choices keeps forcing me back to an option I had made beforehand
Good game... Hope, i do, that a sequel is forthcoming...

I'm coming back to purchase this game again five years later. One of my favorite stories on "Choice of Games" website, not the best available and a bit short, but one of my top choices. A good story for a couple hours of entertainment.
I tried this twice with a few years in between. I paid for the whole story, but I just can't get into it. The story and characters just aren't that interesting. Maybe it gets better later.
Didn't expect that twist. Awesome story.

Started out great, you finish the first part of the story and are excited that you are about to start the real adventure. Then poof. The game is over at the flip of a few pages it felt like with a out of the blue curve ball ending. This story had so much potential but ultimately it was half assed.
Poorly written & superficial
just wow!!

The plot might have been a bit railroaded but the story had some merits. I greatly appreciate how this author uses the stats system as a characterization tool– as it should be. The writing can get cheesy though.
i was hoping this story could be longer but its ok. anyway its a great story and coming in a comparatively cheap price for a masterpiece

this was ok the choices were not that great and the ending left me quite confused. i still really dont understand it. i dont think the price of this was worth the book and its lack of control one would expect to have. one question which always lingered was a learnt magic .. bearly used it and suddenly im the greatest magic user in the world .. did not give me enough opportunities to use magic or what i could do with magic, was quite a strange and slightly dissapointed story .. for me at least.
Fun story to read! not everything is as it seems! different endings! Narrative as a lot of humor.
love it, the only problem is its not very replayable and is too short which isnt really a bad the but hay i would still recamend this game to first time players of the CYOA game style.

userName: Please help Jimmy has a gun
content: really good nuff said.
hated it at first. and i hated the statuses system. but it definitely did not dissapoint. played untill late into the night. Would definitely recommend :)
Bought a while ago, and fondly remembered as one of the good CYOA games. Worth the redownload and replay, and would be worth the buy!
One of the best CYOA books on Play Store. Looking for a good fantasy story? Start here.
wish it was my real life
Loved it man

I got Fatehaven when it first came out. It has been one of, if not my favorite game I have purchased since. The story is intriguing, fun, and full of depth. I would suggest this game to anyone who likes fantasy stories, and even those that usually don't.
This is an amazing story, and i particularly like how the different powers can affect some scenarios, definatly replayable as i have several run throughs.
One of the better CYOA books available compelling story with a good sense of humour.
Very fun game... I wish I could have become a elf my self and pick what I was. But the ending could be better tho , but over all I rate it at a 5 *.
Absolutely amazing story and characters, great length, and easily worth the money. Loved it completely.
Please make a part 2! This novel game was by far my favorite one.
Amazing. It's kind of long at parts and the ending leaves me a little disatisfied, but on a whole this is worth the read. Great characters and good story.
OMFG I love you whoever made this story
Hands down the best "Choose Your Own Story" game I have every played! Great dialogue, realistic decisions, great storyline and writting, super fun, and decently long. Buy it, play it.

Big fan of the author's other book series "Samurai of Hyuga". This one is just as great in my opinion. The characters are interesting and the story is very engaging. Worth replaying to see all the paths as well.

I liked it but it felt short. It had so much potential; so much hype and thrill to be used and yet it fell short. The characters were good enough though I wish there were more interactions between the supposed love interests as well as the other side characters. Again I liked it so there.

On the one hand, this is more linear than I usually like my choice games, without much replayability value. But it's a fun yarn, especially Patch--and the twist is brilliant, one of the most delightfully meta moments in any CoG/HG so far.

The whole concept of the story is great but it has an unsuccessful attempt to force tragedy upon the protagonist, an ugly twist, and a rushed ending. If refined further, it will become a masterpiece. Overalĺ, it's actually ok but not worth the money.

Well, I think it's the same author as Samurai of Hyuga, and it shows. The choices are shallow, it's some times very hard to guess which action will bump which characteristic as you're not in the author's head, and, anyway, they don't impact the story apart for some fluff text. I also feel like the author is quite bad at world building. It feels like the story is a set of action scenes lightly tied together with a story, but you never really feel like a part of the whole. On the bright side, the action parts are extremely well done, the author is adept at creating tension and cinematic scenes. I also enjoy the writing style, which is clear and concise, and doesn't get in the way of enjoying the story (if I did enjoy it).

When I played the available demo, I didnt like this. The story was told in a way that made me think of the word juvenille. I was bored and shed the $3. Who would have thought I actually turn to like it. While in a sense it is rather juvenille, it also far more interesting than I gave it credit for. Made me wonder if it was done on purpose as distraction for the climax (sigh thx to this now this sentence sounded dirty)

I loved the story and the characters. They all feel so alive. The ending 
was amazing too. I cried a little.
Awesome you should make a squeal!

Can't Believe it ...its almost unbelievable how good a story could be ,then 
ending made a great effort to make this story a glorious one !!
THE BEST hosted games project ever! Definitely worth the money

Not a fan of the writing style. Adventure story that self-references itself 
too much.

Slightly above average. It could have been just a book instead of having 
choices. Characters werent that interesting and didn't find myself caring 
about them. The twist at the end was good though
Nice
One of my favorite stories from HG

This is one of the best text based games I've ever played the end twist 
throughs you and the scene with Lillian is a good move

I absolutely loved this story. The twists and turns kept me on my toes as 
well as the action. I got a very satisfying ending and can't wait to find 
out what story I get with different choices made in a second playthrough. 
Thank you the rollarcoaster ride.
Loved it! Wish it was a bit longer though.

Great story. The storyline (as in what you experience throughout the story) 
doesn't change all that much, but I like that you can decide your ending. A 
little short for me, but overall was very enjoyable.

Wow. That's what this interactive story is. The character and everything. 
Especially with the ending. I have to take a moment of silence to think 
about it for a moment my mom even got worried saying i was spacing out so 
suddenly. Well the reason i gave it gour star is bcause i dont really 
understand the gnomes and the accents. So dont really know the exact word 
but got the gist of it.

Was a good game albeit short, I thought it was worth its cost but mileage 
may vary in that department since replay value is minimal in my experience.

Maybe worth it years ago but in 2018, it's not worth the price. Skip unless 
you are bored and are ok spending money AND have played all of the new and 
more recent games that are out
Disappointing. You have no control over what happens in the story, and no choice on what you feel about the events. I regret buying this.
Great story loved the twist at the end!

It's all I wanted. Very story driven and very choice driven, there is action and a good amount of it but I felt like I wanted to be MORE, more of a fighter. And if you're worried about wasting your money on a shorter game, don't worry this is pretty long. I only wished that I could both be more of a physical fighter and that it didn't do that time skip.
One of the best games I've played in a while
Would love to see a sequence series. Reminded me of ATLA when I was growing up and would like to see it as a full series. Keep up the great writing.
An amazing story thst is worth playing
Best choices game I've ever played! Everything was extremely interesting and thought out and the ending is just amazing..can't wait for more games like this in the future!
Great story.
I have to admit, the story is amazing and worth the money, but it's too short. I just wish it was a little longer, and give you more choices.

OMG I totally didn't see the twist ending coming! Some people complain it's too short, but that's because they breeze through it like no tomorrow. If you actually think carefully when you chose your choices and try to get what the text is hinting at, this game lasts waaaaay longer than 4 hours. Love this story ever since it's first published. The writing style is both charming and perverted, but in a good way cause it lightens the mood of the story especially at serious parts (there's quite a lot of serious parts) and makes the story still fun to read. Bregan/Brigid is such a short-tempered but cute cinnamon roll! OMG, if I'm getting a cat, boy girl I don't care, I'm naming that thing Patch.

Started reading this while i wait for more samurai of hyuga and so glad i did. Its such a good story and i really like the writing style. Action is so well described and characters are well built. I just completed my first play through the twist was very good and kept me speculating right up to the end. So really looking forward to completing the other endings
Amazing story.  I would love a little longer conclusion but after the twist it feels rushed.  I loved the characters, the story,  the choices.  Overall top ten cyoa game
The humor is definitely a good selling point, the story seems interesting so far but as long as it keeps being funny it's worth the price.

I absolutely loved it! I fell in love with the characters--the work put into them is astounding and well-detailed. And that curveball at the end really threw me for a loop! Overall, a great story that I highly recommend anyone looking for a good adventure to read.
One of the best endings ever, loved it, would love a movie to be made on this lmao

I absolutely loved it! I really love these types of games, unfortunately I am very picky, and it's hard to find ones I like. But I just fell in love with this one! I wish it could keep going, the twist at the end was very interesting. I tend to have a propensity for Orcs so I was very excited to see that I can incorporate that into my story. (I naturally romanced my Orc BFF. ;) )  I was excited to see the teasing moments between the two, it was very fun. A+!
I really wish I could get my money back for this one. The plot had potential but the story itself wasn't good.
One of the best choose your own adventures that I've read out of all of the stories that I can get on here.
Loved it. Worth every cent; very well made.

Loved it. Interesting characters, amazing storyline, awesome fight scenes, great romances. Loved the similarities between this and The Lost Heir, Brigid as Petra, Patch/Lillian as Gale, Silvana as Jess (Soulburners forever!) And Kaine as Zuzak. Totally worth the money.

This was an interesting story with a lot of good points and a twist I didn't see coming. On the other hand there are times where choice could have been left to the player but instead the author will spend a few pages telling you what you are doing. The characters were likable and the romances were good but they could have been fleshed out a bit more (especially Silvanus). I also didn't like how your character has constant dirty thoughts whether you choose it or not, felt a little immature at times tbh. This is enjoyable and entertaining, I don't mind having paid for it at all cos work has gone into this and it's worth a go but I've played stronger stories for less or at least been able to play the first chapter free to get a feel for it. I would recommend this if you love cyoa though.
I really find it a great game - though some things have effects or require stats that I didn't expect. Other than that, it's wonderful.

On par with the lost heir. Loved the story, and the fleshed out characters. The romance is always a plus. Hosted games is one of my best discoveries as of yet! Silvana remind ed me of Jess so much. Miss and love you Jess! Soulburners for life!
Totally worth it!

I fell in love with this game its one of the best i ever played and to be honest its the first one i ever payed for and im so happy i did and just wish there was more Romance and Love but overrall Its The best one ever

This is hands down my favourite hosted/choice of game out of them all. The story pulls you in, you care about all the characters and the writing has blown me away. I highly recommend this, you won't be disappointed!!!
A fun story to play through and a good way to kill time
Started out very strong, but the end felt rushed and unfinished.  Fun, but not $3 fun.
Enjoyable to read, but I prefer more frequent choices with these.

A single playthrough took me one hour, not four, and didn't like the ending. Tried different choices but got the same one. Also disappointed that an interesting potential romance option dies at a certain point no matter what I chose.
Intriguing characters and meaningful choices makes this story/CYOA stand out among the rest. Also, that ending always surprises me even after I've played this many times. 👌

Great Game to Keep you busy for some time. Good Narration coupled with a somewhat unusual story and some twists, even if somewhat far- fetched make for a quite satisfying read and play. Definitely got my money's worth and way more.
Perfect. Leaves little in the way of improvement. Exceedingly well written, all plot twists earn the right to be called such. The whole story is well done.

Just a small thing to say: Loved it. You got me with that twist near the end there, had me a bit heartbroken due to a particular choice I made before that point. Played it straight and true. In which I mean no multiple restarts. Been really careful with my choices and managed to get a "Fantastic" ending result. Still a little heartbroken though (~‾▿‾)~
One of my favorites of all time!
The narration was simply not for me, and I couldn't understand how my PC who loved the Church, suddenly betrayed them to protect someone who admitted they were a Witch.
Absolutely brilliant couldnt put it down and really long solid story

Very poorly thought out. Among the worst offences are that the game keeps forgetting that you're a mage, so that, among other things, one friend can get killed "dramatically", and another has a "dramatic" fight. It would have been trivial for your character to kill the attackers with magic, but no, that would be sane, and thus the author won't allow that. Another failing is that the game assumes that you don't want to kill the mastermind, even right after you slaughter their henchman. I absolutely regret this purchase.
Incredibly well-created and in-depth storytelling.

Terrible. Game starts off interesting...then basically puts you on the bench while the writer proceeds to decide what your character says, feels about other characters, does, and even thinks, which is often perverted. Perverted would have been fine if it was cause the player decided to be that way but its like that no matter how you try to craft your character. This is yet another story where the writer is more interested in telling their own story rather than caring about being a choice game and letting the player have valid input.

I don't write many reviews, but I had to for this. I have played many CYOA games but I have never enjoyed one so much until now.   Fatehaven has an enticing story, likeable characters, and a great narration. I was laughing one moment, and tearing up the next, then laughing again. It takes a great writer to be able to do that.   There isn't much replay value but the one playthrough is enough to experience what makes the game so great.   I look forward to whatever this author has in store next.
The story line is wonderful! It had great depth, and you have many choices! It's well worth the money!

the character and story are believable and likable.    the main story is pretty much linear with some minor changes with your choices and only the ending has a more meaningful difference depending on your critical stat and romance option.    the ending felt kinda rushed as compare to the introduction which is a pity. i would like to know more about the characters and their after story.   Dont worry about messing up in the story because you can always restart the game. which is what i did over and over again and memorising the correct option along the way.   *minor spoiler* the plot twist about the main girl, silvana,  is both the climax and awkward. There are no foreshadowing as to what she is up to.   It isn't unbelievable but just felt out of place.  ****************  the games sometimes uses phrases that are hard to understand like... five hell", "welcome to fatehaven", "fatehaven companion".  which left me guessing what they mean till now.  Note that the "fatehaven" here most likely doesn't mean the game itself.   In the end,  the game is pretty much well done and can easily draw you into the story. however, the plot twist might not be as well structured as you hope to be. largely Linear storyline with branching endings and minor narrative changes based on your choice.  4/5 game.  worth your time
I LIKED IT, But I get stuck on some parts. I wished that it was a little bit easy at some parts.

Charming!  Probably the simplest, yet most entertaining choice-based game I have ever played. While most interactive novels can be a bit of a slog to get through (often discouraging me from attempting several playthroughs) and have the tendency of taking themselves too seriously - "Fateshaven" is a fun adventure with loads of heart, that isn't afraid to be self-aware or humorous. Characters are identifiable and likeable, even if the secondary ones seem to be more developed than the main ones. Storytelling is good but unbalanced; the beginning chapters go on for much too long. Romance options are sweet but feel somewhat hollow, needed more development. Options are few and feel lazily put together, more and more thoughtful ones would have been nice. Nevertheless, very replayable; worth every penny.
Fun af

At first it was pretty good but towards the end it kinda just became dull and is alright for the first read but rereads are no loger intresting and spoilers at the end the time loop is actully just different players this is because of the black mage saying that the MC had huge personality differences per every time loop.

Ending was a little rushed but the story was very appealing. Choices actually somewhat mattered but there was still a relatively interesting plotline going on as well. The narration was very funny and somewhat lewd descriptions added entertainment.
Please give me more, this was awesome.
This game has my heart in pieces!!! totally In love with every character!! it's a game I'd play over and over ^-^
Good game and Warren's multiple play throughs
It was a fun experience but it was very lewd in places (almost unnecessarily so) and the ending felt a little anticlimactic. The "check vs"  system really broke the immersion as well.
The characters were so intruiging and so qas the story! You shoukd totes buy it, its srsly worth the money
Great story, very interesting

I was scared I would have to put a one star here, but I'm glad everything worked out. Great story. Great characters. SO GOOD. However, I would like a kind of check up on the characters after the story. I know you have one for the main character and any characters they might marry. But I'd like to know about the others too.
Enjoyed but seemed a little rushed at the end overall good experience tho, i like the check versus whatever mechanic.

It is a great rpg with the quality of a high end fantasy novel. Probably one of if not the best cyoa ive ever played and one of the best games and books ive played and read. I tremendously recommend this experience.
Boring story i forced myself through it. Narrator trying to be funny but isnt. Few choices which dont matter that much. Overall i regret spending £2 on it there are much better ones that are free.
I just wanted to say I enjoyed all of it. The story line, characters, all of it
Funny and an interesting ending. I highly recommend it.

I loved all the interesting and complexed characters, the three romance options are strong. My first play through I got with Bridget, and got really emotional when Patch died. This time I'm going to do it with the kitten and see what happens.
Now I'll try not to spoil things, but I will say that this story very quickly goes from generic to Sixth Sense-ish. It's definitely worth a read.
Its so good that it needs to ve nerfed! But all seriousness, it was amazing and i cant wait for more of your futre work.
That plot twist at the end blow my mind, it was as if I suddenly started playing the Stanley Parable or something, anyways glad I lived a happy life in the end with my neko, awesome game

Worth the money. I love magic and fantasy... let's not forget romance! But it lacked in romance. Took me all game to finally get my guy. Though the plot was amazing and I'm very impressed. I'd love more magic but the MC was strong and I felt like I made her turn into me. I'm impressed over all and can't complain. Some parts where boring but like any book there's always a little part like that and I might have just chosen that path myself in the book. Amazing read. I'm gonna go look for the other books.

And I really cared about the characters and what happened to them. The plot twist was amazing and the romance was good although choosing Patch is a bad idea. I wish you could decide who died by making the one who goes in one of the positions the one that dies.
The game is very nice but far too short for my tastes. Would be more worth buying if it was expanded upon but still recommended.
This is an amazing interactive novel! Worth every cent!
I liked the storyline but there wasn't enough choices and it felt like each page would take forever to read.
Truly reccomend it! It's engaging and love the plot :D
Played through almost all the choice apps in the store and loved this one!
I've played through multiple times and gotten different endings each time, very satisfying and entertaining.

I liked the game even though most of the choices were based on two things that are easily picked by your stats but the ending wasn't great almost going out of its way to insolt you the reader and lable you as a villian for picking the choices be them good or bad
Don't worry about your 'stats'.  Play it as yourself, and as yourself only,  and it'll surprise you.  Thank you, for letting me enjoy this with $6.
HOw dare you make me cry at the ending.
The story is great i wish me and that guy switched lives well at least some of the time
Story driven action and adventure!
I was sad that patch died but other than that it was amazing and I love it I wish they will make a second one about after you stop the meteor.
It's good just not much of a good story
The story is really weird and interesting.

It was fun yeah but it still a linear story, it doesn't really give you a way to change the ending only who you and it with. Also by the way it's described I thought I'd be able to romance with one of the characters but nope I was not.

It's a well-written story, and it's definitely worth reading, but the world hardly seems original. A land called Delmacia? One letter off from Riot's Demacia. Orcs have tusks and green skin? Blizzard's Warcraft did that. Silvana the dark magician? Sylvanas from Warcraft is a banshee. I could go on, but you see what I'm driving at. Oh, and just so I'm clear:  Borrowing ideas is perfectly reasonable. Taking them wholesale, less so. Also, four-hour play? If you read super-slowly...

I love it, all the other way through good characters and interesting situations. But I am sorely disappointed in the ending. First not only did you make all of the events that transpired caused by a meteorite that's going to destroy the world but also make it a time traveling mess that makes all our past choices void I couldn't even get myself to pick it up and play it again

I, as a seeker of my own adventure, have bought and read many types of books such as this and I have only one thing to say about it... It is the greatest book I have ever read in my life so far. I wish to give my personal thanks to the men and women who wrote this story and hope to have even more awesome books such as this in the future. Thank you for all your hard work into making making a masterpiece such as this.
L.O.V.E.D.I.T
I liked everything, despite the ending feeling lack luster
Fell in love. Just... Even as i reminic, my heart aches.
Very interesting :-)

one of the best interactive stories ive read so far dialog one the protagonist side could be cleared up a bit didnt really know when my character was talking or when it was just thinking or explanation
Quite an enjoyable story with numerous choices. One star off for lack of distinction between stats and I had no clue when the main char was talking and when he was just thinking.
Love it
My only problem is how the story is written..if it was written in more of a simpler way I think I would of enjoyed it more..like for example 'the life of a wizard' was a lot easier to read than this.
Loved the story. Think it should have a sequel.

But why, when it asks what you think about religion, does it consider the, 'They're just a means of control!' option to bring up your emotional score? Wouldn't you think it was the opposite? That irked me.
Just good and worth buying
Sadly the choices don't seem to have any real impact. There is very little variation. It was still a very good read though. Hope to see more of this author.
Some grammatical errors, but I really enjoyed the story.
Really really good story. Best hosted game since Zombie Exodus!!

I've enjoyed many CoG titles, but this was a surprising and awesome one. It was a lot longer than I expected and had some amazing depth. More creative than most too, in my opinion. Oh, and pretty good romantic choices.

I did not find any dragon in the story. Although the plot twists is good. Spoiler alert! As far as I know there are 3 ending for each girl. 1 single ending. 2 dead(killing your friend and get your soul pulled out ) There is no Dragon????!!! Why would you put it in the opening when there is none?
I just love this so much. Wish there were more stories like this or maybe a sequel
I wish the skill system wasn't so complicated or so quickly subject to change. Also, the same story could have been written with common English...

Dissapointing. The start was intrialguingbwith 3/4,choifes. But afterward, You can't called this choice of games if you can only pick one between 2 choices. This is practically just a novel. Your choice also did not influence where the story goes. Or even your character. Replayability also only interesting for a first timer. Waste of my money.... Too bad...
this story hit the ground running but quickly lost steam - a great read but it feels like its missing the middle of the story
Worth your money loved it loved it loved it great story, I just wish it was longer or had a second part

I really liked the story but it did disappointed me a bit. I've tried going through the multiple endings and was disappointed by the fact if how little the story line changes when you have a different element. Makes sense but still there were only small changes to the storyline making the replies boring. In addition to that, is there even an ending where you can get fully corrupted?  I've tried multiple times with only getting around 70% would have really loved it if there was an ending for it though.
Can not recommended this choose your own adventure game enough it has to be one of if not the best stories out there
Lack of choice is made up by great storytelling!
Wroth every dollar. The story was engrossing and humorous. Another great job by Hosted Games

It was beautifully written and the plot twist at the end was amazing. I thought the game was good but I did not expect it to be this great. I've been playing it over and over to try and get every different end. The only thing I would have preferred is if the options would list what stats it gives you or at least what stats you need to fulfil it without failing, but that might take something out of the game. Overall it was a beautiful game and I cannot stress that enough. I'll definitely be looking for more.

Good idea for a story. However the author is just not a good writer, too many long-winded descriptions and tries to be funny but fails. Little to no choice, and a very disappointing ending. Save your money.
ending could be better
I think this is fun, however I can't seem to get the fire element as my magic element. I can get the other 3 though any tips on how to get it. Or is it not really there.
Great fun.

Was amazing. It worked like a Telltale game but it didn't have that annoying fact of your decisions meaning absolutely nothing. They actually had consequences and advantages and they lingered. The story I played was just awesome...I loved it.
It gives illusions of 'choice' that doesn't alter the story at all..

You have to love this one, it changes with each choice you make and it give your element based on your personality. My suggestions though should be that it needs to be grammer checked, and a suggestion.... if you played as all the elements then their should be the option to have the story give you a special 5th element like lightning or something amazing like that :)
Love it one of the best if read so far
Absolutely loved it, can't get enough of it!

I have come to expect a high level of story-telling from Hosted games and this one is no exception. The story is well written and pretty captivating.  However,  the choices in this game really don't make that much of a difference in the story. I enjoyed it still. Looking forward to more to come.

While the world and writing is great there is not much of it and virtually no choice. The story was nearly identical save the end and even then there was only tiny room for variation. Not worth the amount I paid but I enjoyed my first playthrough and hope to see more from the author.
This is by far my favorite story in this genera. Great twist and turn out. Good job Guys!

However, I have to remove a star for 2 reasons.  First, four hours for a single play through?  Make that one hour.  One hour isn't bad, but claiming four hours and not delivering was disappointing.  Second, the story was pretty railroaded.  Your choices made paragraphs change here and there, but you only really see a difference at the end.

Set in a fantasy world where magic is taboo, you being a mage is handled well, and the characters you meet along the way are quirky, though a bit shallow. The price the game is set at is just right, as it is a lengthy, enjoyable tale, though not quite as long as games like Tin star. Those looking to buy should definitely do so, but I would play through the demo in the CoG website first to see if it's for you.
